          {
            "text": "Fry the onion and potato",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{unsalted-butter}} of butter",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " and ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{olive-oil}} of olive oil",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " in a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Add the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{onion}} onions",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " and cook for 8 minutes until golden. Add the crushed potato, season with ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "{{black-pepper}}",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": " and press flat. Cook without disturbing for 5 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Add the corned beef and crisp",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Break the corned beef into large chunks and scatter over the potato. Add the Worcestershire sauce if using. Stir everything together roughly, then press flat again. Cook for 5 minutes until the base develops a deep brown crust. Turn in sections, scraping up the crust, and cook for another 5 minutes to crisp the other side.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "rows": [
            {
              "fix": "Use a large pan over high heat. Ensure the potato is fully cold and dry before it goes in.",
              "cause": "Pan not hot enough, or too much liquid in the potato",
              "symptom": "Hash is soft and grey with no crust"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Leave the corned beef in larger pieces and stir only once, to turn the crust.",
              "cause": "Broken into pieces too small, or stirred too often",
              "symptom": "Corned beef disintegrates completely"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Do not salt the hash during cooking. Serve with something acidic such as ketchup or pickled cabbage to balance.",
              "cause": "Corned beef is already highly salted; no extra salt is needed",
              "symptom": "Hash is very salty"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Reduce to medium heat after the initial browning.",
              "cause": "Heat too high",
              "symptom": "Bottom is burnt before the top is hot through"
            }
          ]
        },
        "content": []
